   \code{tree_fusing} \tab Enabled (defaults) \cr
   \code{tree_hybridizing} \tab Disabled (\code{rounds = 0}) \cr
   \code{tree_drifting} \tab Enabled (\code{iterations = 5}) \cr
   \code{ratchet} \tab Disabled (\code{iterations = 0}) \cr
   \code{set_only} \tab \code{FALSE} \cr
}

}

\subsection{Strategy configuration}{

Each sub-strategy is configured via its own command object. Strategies
can be disabled by setting their iteration or round count to zero:
\itemize{
\item \verb{$ratchet$iterations <- 0} — disable the ratchet.
\item \verb{$tree_drifting$iterations <- 0} — disable tree drifting.
\item \verb{$tree_fusing$rounds <- 0} — disable tree fusing.
\item \verb{$tree_hybridizing$rounds <- 0} — disable tree hybridizing.
}

Setting a strategy field to \code{NULL} resets it to its default
configuration.
}

\subsection{Queue integration}{

Calling \verb{$enqueue()} adds this command to a \link{CommandQueue} and also
enqueues each enabled sub-strategy in set-only mode at priority \code{500},
so their parameters are configured before the driven search executes at
priority \code{501}.
}

\subsection{Command output}{

\verb{$render()} produces a string of the form
\verb{xmult= replications \{replications\} hits \{hits\} ...;}
}
}
\examples{
# Create with default settings
xm <- ExtraSearchMethodsCommand$new()

# Increase replications and require more hits
xm$replications <- 10
xm$hits <- 3

# Enable the ratchet
xm$ratchet$iterations <- 20

# Disable tree drifting
xm$tree_drifting$iterations <- 0

# View full configuration
xm$format()

# Generate the TNT command
xm$render()

}
